From mtmorg@n@b|oc @end|ng |rom gm@||@com  Thu Jul 16 21:31:52 2020
From: mtmorg@n@b|oc @end|ng |rom gm@||@com (Martin Morgan)
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2020 19:31:52 +0000
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Package submission with strong external dependency
 during build/check [take 2]
In-Reply-To: <57e164dfb5e5406a9367b3692a6e0214@ul-exc-pr-mbx12.ulaval.ca>
References: <57e164dfb5e5406a9367b3692a6e0214@ul-exc-pr-mbx12.ulaval.ca>
Message-ID: <BL0PR04MB6609AA19E3FB3866DCFBE0DAF97F0@BL0PR04MB6609.namprd04.prod.outlook.com>

This set up is not possible in Bioconductor.

I suggest that you explore the use of 'mocks' so that your code thinks, during testing and examples, that it is querying an elasticsearch server, but is actually checking that it can send the appropriate message / interpret the expected response -- you're testing your R code, not the elasticsearch implementation.

There is some more information at

  https://books.ropensci.org/http-testing/

